What we call unselfishness is, rather than humility‚ often spoken of as love's requisite, but when we pause we know this to be a slovenly manner of thought, because selfishness is noble or ignoble as it is or is not instigated by pride. Lack of due and humble care for self is most inimical to love, but humility is never thus inimical. Jesus allowed no affection —not even his mother’s——to interfere with his mission.
